To **set up / install / build** this project, read and execute the repo-root `INSTALL.md` top-to-bottom.
It is the single authoritative, ordered runbook. Do **not** follow the older `docs/INSTALL.md` (stale).

Project & collaboration rules: see `CLAUDE.md`.

Must-knows:
- Python is **`py -3.11`** (do not use bare `python` or `npm run test:python`).
- Clone with **`--recurse-submodules`** (submodules: `vendor/AI4BI`, `vendor/LV`, `plugins/cim-modules`).
- **Labeling (ANnoTation) is a directory junction, not a submodule.**
- The **Tauri shell** now lives in-repo at `apps/host-tauri/` and ships a prebuilt runnable binary (`apps/host-tauri/prebuilt/cim-light.exe`) — daily use needs no sibling clone, no npm install, no Rust toolchain. To **rebuild** the Rust shell (rare), run `npm install` + `npm run tauri:build` in `apps/host-tauri/` on a machine **without WDAC enforce**, then replace `apps/host-tauri/prebuilt/cim-light.exe`.
